President Obama and Prime Minister Najib of Malaysia held a joint press conference in Kuala Lumpur. The leaders discussed the ongoing search for Malaysia Airlines Flight 370 and the need for transparency in the investigation. They also discussed the strengthening of economic and security ties between the US and Malaysia, as well as the importance of upholding international law in the South China Sea. President Obama expressed his support for Malaysia's efforts in political reform and the respect for human rights. The leaders also discussed the Trans-Pacific Partnership (TPP) and the potential benefits of the trade deal for both countries. Finally, President Obama addressed the issue of racially-charged comments made by the owner of the Los Angeles Clippers basketball team, expressing his confidence that the NBA would address the issue.